=== {rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

Inscribes a reliquary into the
{rbtgi_depot}:
mirrors upstream tool images into a datestamped GAR namespace
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDI-depot_inscribe.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_director_yoke]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_director_yoke}

Yokes a reliquary stamp into a conjure vessel's
{rbrv_regime}:
validates the stamp against GAR and the vessel against its enrollment, then rewrites `RBRV_RELIQUARY` in the vessel's `rbrv.env`
({rbtgog_depot}).

include::RBSDY-director_yoke.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_delete]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_delete}

Jettisons a single
{rbtgi_image}
artifact by
{rbst_locator}
({rbtgog_image}).
Locator-generic across hallmark members, reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.

include::RBSIJ-image_jettison.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_retrieve]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_retrieve}

Wrests a single
{rbtgi_image}
artifact by
{rbst_locator}
({rbtgog_image}).
Locator-generic across hallmark members, reliquary tool images, and enshrinement images.
{rbtr_director}-tier — peer to {rbtgo_image_delete}, distinct from {rbtgo_ark_summon}.

include::RBSIW-image_wrest.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_rekon]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_rekon}

Reports canonical-member presence under a hallmark or reliquary subtree in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_image}).
Two distinct procedures (`rbfl_rekon_hallmark`, `rbfl_rekon_reliquary`); rekon-on-enshrinement is intentionally omitted (enshrinements are 1-deep).

include::RBSIR-image_rekon.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_image_audit]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_image_audit}

Lists identifiers under one of three GAR domains (hallmarks, reliquaries, enshrinements) in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_image}).
{rbtr_director}-tier flat catalog; complements the {rbtr_retriever}-tier {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}, which adds health classification on the hallmark domain only.

include::RBSIA-image_audit.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_abjure]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_abjure}

Formally renounces an
{rbtga_ark}
from the repository
({rbtgog_ark}),
removing its image, about, and vouch artifacts as a coherent unit.

include::RBSAA-ark_abjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_ordain]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_ordain}

Ordains a hallmark from a vessel — the master ceremony dispatch operation.
Detects vessel mode (conjure, bind, or graft) and delegates to the appropriate
{rbtga_ark}
creation path, then chains metadata and vouch pipeline stages.

[[rbtgo_ark_conjure]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_conjure}

Conjures an
{rbtga_ark_image}
by building a container image
({rbtgog_ark})
from a vessel specification.
Build context delivered via {rbtga_ark_pouch}, submitted via `builds.create` API. The combined job produces both the `image` and `about` packages under the hallmark subtree (about steps embedded via stitch). Vouch is a separate Cloud Build job using DSSE envelope signature verification.

include::RBSAC-ark_conjure.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_enshrine]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_enshrine}

Enshrines upstream base images into
{gar_service}
({rbtgog_ark}),
producing content-addressed
{rbrv_image_anchor}
references from
{rbrv_image_origin}
declarations.
The
{rbtr_director}
submits a Cloud Build job that copies each upstream image by tag to GAR with a human-readable anchor tag, and writes the anchor back to the vessel regime.

include::RBSAE-ark_enshrine.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_graft]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_graft}

Grafts a locally-built container image into the
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark})
via native docker/podman push.
The image push itself is local (no Cloud Build); about and vouch follow as Cloud Build jobs.

include::RBSAG-ark_graft.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_about]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_about}

Assembles the
{rbtga_ark_about}
metadata artifact for an existing
{rbtga_ark_image}
({rbtgog_ark}).
Runs Syft for SBOM generation and builds mode-aware `build_info.json` using uniform
{gcb_service}
steps.
Conjure and bind embed these steps in their primary Cloud Build job alongside image production; graft's primary job consists of these steps alone.

include::RBSAB-ark_about.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_vouch]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_ark_vouch}

Vouches for an
{rbtga_ark}
({rbtgog_ark}),
producing a
{rbtga_ark_vouch}
that records mode-aware verification results.
Conjure: DSSE envelope signature verification (Python 3 + openssl against GCB attestor keys).
Bind: digest-pin comparison.
Graft: GRAFTED stamp.
Submitted as a
{gcb_service}
job via `builds.create` after
{rbtgo_ark_about}
completes.

include::RBSAV-ark_vouch.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_director_vouch]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_director_vouch}

Batch-vouches every pending
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark}).
Dispatches {rbtgo_ark_vouch} per pending hallmark; mode-specific verification (conjure, bind, graft) happens inside that operation, not in the batch.
Any vouch failure terminates the batch fail-fast at the broken hallmark.

include::RBSDV-director_vouch.adoc[]

== {rbtr_retriever} Operations

[[rbtgo_hallmark_tally]]
//axvo_method axd_transient axd_grouped
=== {rbtgo_hallmark_tally}

Enumerates every
{rbtga_ark}
hallmark in
{rbtgi_repository}
({rbtgog_ark}),
classifying each by artifact completeness and vouch status.

include::RBSCL-consecration_tally.adoc[]

[[rbtgo_ark_summon]]

//axhob_operation
{rbtgo_director_yoke}

NOTE: This operation writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«STAMP»` into a conjure vessel's `rbrv.env` so that subsequent Cloud Build operations (conjure, enshrine) consume the named tool image set as GCB step images.
Both arguments are validated before any file write: the stamp against GAR (all six tool packages must be present under the reliquary subtree), the vessel against its RBRV enrollment plus a vessel-mode gate.
On validation failure the operation errors diagnostically without touching any file.

The
{rbtr_director}
yokes a reliquary stamp into a vessel's regime:

//axhopt_typed_parameter
{rbtr_director}
. *Validate Input Parameters*:
.. {rbbc_require}
`«VESSEL_SIGIL»` provided as folio (e.g., `rbev-sentry-deb-tether`)
.. {rbbc_require}
`«STAMP»` provided as first positional argument (e.g., `r260327172456`)

//axhos_step
. *Load Vessel* (CLI furnish, BUZ_FOLIO-gated):
.. Resolve `«VESSEL_SIGIL»` to vessel directory `${RBRR_VESSEL_DIR}/«VESSEL_SIGIL»`
.. {rbbc_require}
vessel directory contains `rbrv.env`
.. Source `rbrv.env` to populate `RBRV_*` variables
.. Kindle RBRV enrollment (no enforce — yoke writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY`,
which is a kindle constant with min=1 enrollment; pre-write enforce
would self-veto on marshal-zero state. The strict validator path is
`rbw-rvv` ValidateVesselRegime.)

//axhos_step
. *Gate on Vessel Mode*:
.. {rbbc_require}
{rbrv_vessel_mode}
equals
{rbrv_vessel_mode_conjure}
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if mode is
{rbrv_vessel_mode_bind}
— bind vessels pin an upstream digest (no Cloud Build, no reliquary)
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if mode is
{rbrv_vessel_mode_graft}
— graft vessels push a locally-built image (no Cloud Build, no reliquary)

//axhos_step
. *Authenticate as
{rbtr_director}*:
.. Execute
{rbtoe_director_authenticate}
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DIRECTOR_TOKEN»` for subsequent API calls

//axhos_step
. *List Reliquary Packages in GAR*:
.. {rbbc_store}
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}d-${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}` (resolved by `RBDC_DEPOT_PROJECT_ID`)
.. {rbbc_store}
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»` as `${RBRR_CLOUD_PREFIX}${RBRR_DEPOT_MONIKER}-gar` (resolved by `RBDC_GAR_REPOSITORY`)
.. {rbbc_call}
link:https://cloud.google.com/artifact-registry/docs/reference/rest/v1/projects.locations.repositories.packages/list[packages.list] for
`«DEPOT_PROJECT_ID»`
/
{rbrr_gcp_region}
/
`«GAR_REPOSITORY»`
with `pageSize=1000`
.. {rbbc_require}
HTTP 200 response
.. Filter response package names to those starting with `{gar_reliquaries_namespace}/«STAMP»/`
.. Strip the subtree prefix to yield the bare tool-name set present in GAR

//axhos_step
. *Verify Tool Image Completeness*:
.. Expected tool name set: `gcloud`, `docker`, `alpine`, `syft`, `binfmt`, `skopeo` (per
{rbtgo_depot_inscribe})
.. {rbbc_require}
all six names present in the filtered list
.. {rbbc_fatal}
if any expected tool is missing — the error message names `«STAMP»`, the reliquary subtree path, and the specific missing tool(s); remediation points at
{rbtgo_depot_inscribe}

//axhos_step
. *Rewrite rbrv.env*:
.. Load the vessel's `rbrv.env` into memory, line by line
.. For each line matching `^RBRV_RELIQUARY=` — substitute with `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«STAMP»`, preserving position
.. All other lines pass through unchanged
.. If no `RBRV_RELIQUARY=` line was found — append one under a `# Tool Image Reliquary` comment header
.. Write the composed content to a temp file, then atomically replace `rbrv.env` via rename

//axhoc_completion
Successful execution writes `RBRV_RELIQUARY=«STAMP»` into the vessel's `rbrv.env`; no GAR state is modified.
The
{rbtr_director}
commits the modified `rbrv.env` with their usual git workflow.

